artist: Rian Treanor with Rotherham Sight & Sound
title_full:
Rian Treanor with Rotherham Sight & Sound

              —
              Action Potential
            
              (Electronic Music Club)
label: Electronic Music Club
description:
OK this is a full madness; visually impaired pensioners Anne Goss (75), Kathleen Allott (74) and Mick Gladwin (65) aka Rotherham Sight & Sound play the music of persistent prism disruptor Rian Treanor with a knockout set of mutant dancehall and mercurial electro-styled zingers, a huge tip if you’re into Autechre, SND, Kakuhan, Iueke, Shubharun Sengupta. 

Rian Treanor keeps knocking new doors of possibility with his new label Electronic Music Club and its initial focus on Rotherham... more

label: SM-LL
description:
London’s anarchists cranks at SM-LL soften up just a little to allow melodic light pierce the brittle electro-dub structures of the 32nd release - def one to check for fans of Vialan, Logos, Bellows 

Cultishly appreciated for their uncompromising approach to raw machine music and collective solidarity, SM-LL here loosen up and lean back into subtly more atmospheric styles. In ‘WAVELET 010’ refractive beams of melody penetrate the surface, illuminating coruscating drums and subsurface details... more
